    {
        "bore/stroke ratio": "Stroke Ratio"
    },
    {
        " is the ratio of the diameter of the piston, or bore , to the length of travel within the cylinder, or stroke . If this is around 1 the engine is said to be square , if it is greater than 1, i.e. the bore is larger than the stroke, it is oversquare . If it is less than 1, i.e. the stroke is larger than the bore, it is undersquare .     Cylinders may be aligned ": null
